# Plan: Add `image-text-to-text` Pipeline to Transformers.js

## Context

Transformers.js exposes a high-level `pipeline()` API that maps task names to pipeline classes.
The library already has `AutoModelForImageTextToText` (supporting LLaVa, Florence2, SmolVLM,
PaliGemma, Qwen2-VL, Idefics3, etc.) defined and exported in `src/models.js`, but no
corresponding pipeline exists. This gap means users cannot use these modern vision-language
models (VLMs) through the standard `pipeline()` API.

The new `image-text-to-text` pipeline accepts a single image and a text prompt, processes both
through the model's processor (which handles image tokenization and prompt construction), then
generates and returns a text response.

---

## Files to Modify

